NPM (Node Package Manager) is the default package manager for Node.js. It helps in: 

Install libraries and packages 
Manage project dependencies 
Run scripts and automation tasks 
Publish your own packages

Command	Description:

npm init	Initialize a new project
npm install	Install all dependencies from package.json
npm install <pkg>	Install a specific package
npm install -g <pkg>	Install a package globally
npm uninstall <pkg>	Remove a package
npm update	Update packages to latest versions
npm outdated	Check for outdated dependencies
npm run <script>	Run a script defined in package.json
npm list	List installed packages
